Dead Redemption 2 Achieves Entertainment's Biggest Opening Weekend of All Time |publisher=[[Business Wire]] |date=October 30, 2018 |accessdate=December 10, 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181030212615/https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20181030005459/en/Red-Dead-Redemption-2-Achieves-Entertainment%E2%80%99s-Biggest |archivedate=October 30, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"MC Best\">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/feature/best-videogames-released-in-2018 |title=Best Video Games of 2018 |last=Dietz |first=Jason |work=[[Metacritic]] |publisher=[[CBS Interactive]] |date=January 2, 2019 |accessdate=October 19, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190918221505/https://www.metacritic.com/feature/best-videogames-released-in-2018 |archivedate=September 18, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"MC PS4\">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-4/red-dead-redemption-2 |title=Red Dead Redemption 2 for PlayStation 4 Reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=October 28, 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190102035209/https://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-4/red-dead-redemption-2 |archivedate=January 2, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"MC XBO\">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/xbox-one/red-dead-redemption-2 |title=Red Dead Redemption 2 for Xbox One Reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=October 28, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190110102903/https://www.metacritic.com/game/xbox-one/red-dead-redemption-2 |archivedate=January 10, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Polygon Sales\">{{cite web |url=https://www.polygon.com/2018/11/7/18073314/red-dead-redemption-2-sales-17-million-units |title=Red Dead Redemption 2 tops 17 million copies shipped |last=Sarkar |first=Samit |website=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |publisher=[[Vox Media]] |date=November 7, 2018 |accessdate=January 5, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181108025709/https://www.polygon.com/2018/11/7/18073314/red-dead-redemption-2-sales-17-million-units |archivedate=November 8, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"THR Sales\">{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/red-dead-redemption-2-breaks-records-725-million-opening-weekend-1156235 |title='Red Dead Redemption 2' Breaks Records With $725 Million Opening Weekend |last=Parker |first=Ryan |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |publisher=[[Eldridge Industries]] |date=October 30, 2018 |accessdate=November 3, 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181030185513/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/red-dead-redemption-2-breaks-records-725-million-opening-weekend-1156235 |archivedate=October 30, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n}}\n\n{{Red Dead}}\n__FORCETOC__\n\n{{featured list}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Accolades received by Red Dead Redemption 2}}\n[[Category:Lists of accolades by video game|Red Dead Redemption 2]]\n[[Category:Red Dead]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use American English|date=October 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Short description|Awards received by the 2018 video game Red Dead Redemption 2}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:List of accolades received by ''Red Dead Redemption 2''}}\n''[[Red Dead Redemption 2]]'' is a [[Western (genre)|Western]]-themed [[action-adventure game]] developed and published by [[Rockstar Games]]. A prequel to the 2010 game ''[[Red Dead Redemption]]'', the game is set in 1899 in a fictionalized representation of the [[Western United States|Western]], [[Midwestern United States|Midwestern]] and [[Southern United States]] and follows [[outlaw]] [[Arthur Morgan (Red Dead)|Arthur Morgan]], a member of the Van der Linde gang. Arthur must deal with the decline of the [[American frontier|Wild West]] whilst attempting to survive against government forces, rival gangs, and other enemies. The game was announced on October 18, 2016, and was widely anticipated.<ref name=\"Announcement\"/> It was nominated for Most Anticipated Game at [[The Game Awards]] in [[The Game Awards 2016|2016]] and [[The Game Awards 2017|2017]],<ref name=\"Game Awards 2016\"/><ref name=\"Game Awards 2017\"/> and for Most Wanted Game at the [[Golden Joystick Awards]].<ref name=\"Golden Joystick 17 Nom\"/>\n\nThe game was released worldwide on October 26, 2018, for the [[PlayStation 4]] and [[Xbox One]] consoles. ''Red Dead Redemption 2'' received \"universal acclaim\" from critics, according to review aggregator [[Metacritic]];{{efn|The game scored an overall [[weighted average]] of 97 out of 100 on [[Metacritic]], based on 98 reviews for the PlayStation 4 version<ref name=\"MC PS4\"/> and 33 reviews for the Xbox One version.<ref name=\"MC XBO\"/>}} it was Metacritic's highest-rated game of 2018.<ref name=\"MC Best\"/> The game had the largest opening weekend in the history of entertainment,<ref name=\"BW Sales\"/> making over $725 million in three days, and selling over 17 million copies in two weeks.<ref name=\"Polygon Sales\"/> Additionally, ''Red Dead Redemption 2'' is the second highest-grossing entertainment launch (behind ''[[Grand Theft Auto V]]'') and set records for largest ever pre-orders, largest first-day sales and largest sales for the first three days in market on [[PlayStation Network]].<ref name=\"THR Sales\"/><ref name=\"BW Sales\"/>\n\n''Red Dead Redemption 2'' garnered awards and nominations in a variety of categories with particular praise for its story, performances, music, and graphical design. At [[The Game Awards 2018]], the game received eight nominations and went on to win four awards: Best Audio Design, Best Narrative, Best Score/Music, and Best Performance for [[Roger Clark (actor, born 1978)|Roger Clark]] as Arthur Morgan.<ref name=\"Game Awards 2018\"/> At ''[[IGN]]''{{'s}} Best of 2018, the game garnered seven nominations,<ref name=\"IGN Art Graphics\">{{cite web|url=https://ign.com/articles/2018/12/10/best-video-game-art-and-graphics-2018|title=Best Video Game Art and Graphics of 2018|date=December 10, 2018|work=[[IGN]]|publisher=[[Ziff Davis]]|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181211175605/https://ign.com/articles/2018/12/10/best-video-game-art-and-graphics-2018|archivedate=December 11, 2018|accessdate=August 6, 2019}}</ref> winning two awards<ref name=\"IGN XBO\">{{cite web|url=https://ign.com/articles/2018/12/10/best-xbox-one-game-2018|title=Best Xbox One Game of 2018|date=December 10, 2018|work=[[IGN]]|publisher=[[Ziff Davis]]|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181211042325/https://ign.com/articles/2018/12/10/best-xbox-one-game-2018|archivedate=December 11, 2018|accessdate=August 6, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"IGN Music\">{{cite web|url=https://ign.com/articles/2018/12/10/best-video-game-music-2018|title=Best Video Game Music of 2018|date=December 10, 2018|work=[[IGN]]|publisher=[[Ziff Davis]]|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181211160939/https://ign.com/articles/2018/12/10/best-video-game-music-2018|archivedate=December 11, 2018|accessdate=August 6, 2019}}</ref> and was named runner-up in four (behind ''[[God of War (2018 video game)|God of War]]'').<ref name=\"IGN GOTY\">{{cite web|url=https://ign.com/articles/2018/12/10/best-game-of-the-year-2018|title=Best Game of the Year 2018|date=December 10, 2018|work=[[IGN]]|publisher=[[Ziff Davis]]|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181211023748/https://ign.com/articles/2018/12/10/best-game-of-the-year-2018|archivedate=December 11, 2018|accessdate=August 6, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"IGN PS4\">{{cite web|url=https://ign.com/articles/2018/12/10/best-playstation-4-game-2018|title=Best PlayStation 4 Game of 2018|date=December 10, 2018|work=[[IGN]]|publisher=[[Ziff Davis]]|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181211023846/https://ign.com/articles/2018/12/10/best-playstation-4-game-2018|archivedate=December 11, 2018|accessdate=August 6, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"IGN Action-Adventure\">{{cite web|url=https://ign.com/articles/2018/12/10/best-action-adventure-game-2018|title=Best Action-Adventure Game of 2018|date=December 10, 2018|work=[[IGN]]|publisher=[[Ziff Davis]]|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181211041735/https://ign.com/articles/2018/12/10/best-action-adventure-game-2018|archivedate=December 11, 2018|accessdate=August 6, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"IGN Story\">{{cite web|url=https://ign.com/articles/2018/12/10/best-video-game-story-2018|title=Best Video Game Story of 2018|date=December 10, 2018|work=[[IGN]]|publisher=[[Ziff Davis]]|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181211162018/https://ign.com/articles/2018/12/10/best-video-game-story-2018|archivedate=December 11, 2018|accessdate=August 6, 2019}}</ref> The game earned eight nominations at the [[22nd Annual D.I.C.E. Awards]], including Game of the Year.<ref name=\"DICE Nom\"/> At the 6th [[SXSW Gaming Awards]], ''Red Dead Redemption 2'' was named the Trending Game of the Year and won for Excellence in SFX and Technical Achievement.<ref name=\"SXSW Win\"/> The game received seven nominations at the [[19th Game Developers Choice Awards]],<ref name=\"GDCA Nom\"/> and six at the [[15th British Academy Games Awards]].<ref name=\"BAFTA\"/> \n\nThe game also appeared on several year-end lists of the best games of 2018, receiving [[Game of the Year]] wins at the Australian Games Awards,<ref name=\"Australian Games Awards\"/> Brazil Game Awards,<ref name=\"Brazil Game Awards\"/> [[Fun & Serious Game Festival]],<ref name=\"Titanium win\"/> Global Game Awards,<ref name=\"Global Game Awards\"/> ''[[IGN Australia]]'' Select Awards,<ref name=\"IGN AU\">{{cite web|url=https://www.au.ign-hub.com/select-awards-2018/|title=Select Awards 2018|date=March 4, 2019|work=[[IGN]]|publisher=[[Ziff Davis]]|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191022065015/https://www.au.ign-hub.com/select-awards-2018/|archivedate=October 22, 2019|accessdate=October 22, 2019}}</ref> and Italian Video Game Awards,<ref name=\"Italian Win\"/> and from outlets such as ''[[4Players]]'',<ref name=\"4Players GOTY\">{{cite web|url=http://www.4players.de/4players.php/spieledesjahres2018/Spiel_des_Jahres_2018/83553.html|title=Spiele des Jahres 2018 \u2013 Spiel des Jahres|date=January 4, 2019|work=[[4Players]]|publisher=[[Computec Media GmbH]]|language=de|trans-title=Games of the Year 2018 \u2013 Game of the Year|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190107062839/http://www.4players.de/4players.php/spieledesjahres2018/Spiel_des_Jahres_2018/83553.html|archivedate=January 7, 2019|accessdate=October 19, 2019}}</ref> ''[[AusGamers]]'',<ref name=\"AusGamers GOTY\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ausgamers.com/features/read/3612429|title=AusGamers Top 10 Best Games of 2018|last=Farrelly|first=Steve|date=January 1, 2019|work=[[AusGamers]]|publisher=AusGamers Pty Ltd|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190112064901/https://www.ausgamers.com/features/read/3612429|archivedate=January 12, 2019|accessdate=October 19, 2019}}</ref> ''[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]'',<ref name=\"Complex GOTY\">{{cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/life/best-video-games-2018/|title=Best Video Games of 2018: Top Games of The Year|last=Wong|first=Kevin|date=December 14, 2018|work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|publisher=[[Complex Media]]|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181214011908/https://www.complex.com/life/best-video-games-2018/|archivedate=December 14, 2018|accessdate=October 19, 2019}}</ref> ''[[Digital Trends]]'',<ref name=\"Digital Trends GOTY\">{{cite web|url=https://www.digitaltrends.com/gaming/best-video-games-2018/|title=The Best Video Games Released in 2018|date=December 12, 2018|work=[[Digital Trends]]|publisher=Designtechnica|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181213115422/https://www.digitaltrends.com/gaming/best-video-games-2018/|archivedate=December 13, 2018|accessdate=October 19, 2019}}</ref> ''[[Edge